# Chasum — Production Environment

Copy to `.env.local` for local development. Set the same keys on the production host for GVM go-live.
See `docs/GVM_GO_LIVE.md` for the full cutover plan.

# Supabase
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your-supabase-project-url
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-supabase-service-role-key
# Optional: for scripts/sync-supabase-email-templates.mjs
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your-supabase-personal-access-token

# App — use the HTTPS production URL in production (auth redirects + email links)
# Must include protocol, no trailing slash. Example: https://chasum.vercel.app
# If left as localhost on Vercel, password reset will fail with "Invalid path…".
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Cron (required in production — protects /api/cron/process-jobs)
# Vercel Cron sends: Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>
CRON_SECRET=your-cron-secret

# Owner Platform (/owner) — comma-separated emails of Chasum super admins
# Also seed platform_admins (migration 014) for database-backed access.
PLATFORM_OWNER_EMAILS=owner@chasum.app

# Email (Resend) — REQUIRED in production for confirmations & reminders
# Without RESEND_API_KEY, production refuses to fake-send (jobs retry / fail).
# Locally, unset key → console logging for development only.
# Also configure Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → SMTP (Resend) for password reset.
RESEND_API_KEY=your-resend-api-key
EMAIL_FROM=Chasum <notifications@yourdomain.com>

# SMS (Twilio) — optional for GVM launch
# Production without Twilio skips SMS (does not pretend to send).
TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID=your-twilio-account-sid
TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN=your-twilio-auth-token
TWILIO_PHONE_NUMBER=+1234567890

# Google Calendar OAuth (optional)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-client-id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your-google-client-secret

# Microsoft Outlook OAuth (optional)
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=your-microsoft-client-id
MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=your-microsoft-client-secret
MICROSOFT_TENANT_ID=common

# AI Receptionist (Emma) — optional. Without OPENAI_API_KEY, Emma uses the
# grounded Chasum-data provider (hours/services/staff/locations/slots only).
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_RECEPTIONIST_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini

# Stripe (optional until card checkout) — never commit live keys
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# Soft schema fallbacks are OFF by default (fail-loud). Enable only for local DBs missing migrations.
# CHASUM_ALLOW_SOFT_SCHEMA=1

# Sentry (optional) — leave empty to no-op
SENTRY_DSN=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
# SENTRY_TRACES_SAMPLE_RATE=0.1

# Inbound delivery webhooks (optional)
RESEND_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
